Introduction
============

Ccal is a calendar program with a curses user interface for terminal
emulators.  It uses readable plain text files for storing the entries.


Compiling
=========

Ccal needs two libraries: nucrsesw and vector. If you don't have
libvector, you can get it from https://github.com/harski/libvector. When
the dependencies are met you can configure and compile ccal with:

$ ./configure.sh
$ make


Installing
==========

Configure and compile ccal, and run

$ make install


Unistalling
===========

$ make uninstall

